üß† HOW TO READ CSS (VERY IMPORTANT FIRST)
selector {
  property: value;
}
üëâ Selector ‚Üí Which element?
üëâ Property ‚Üí What do you want to change?
üëâ Value ‚Üí How much / which type?

=====================================================================
üåç GLOBAL / BASIC CSS
* {
  margin: 0;              /* removes default outer space */
  padding: 0;             /* removes default inner space */
  box-sizing: border-box; /* width includes padding + border */
}
üß† Logic:
Browsers add default spacing. We reset it so we get full control.
======================================================================

üé® COLORS & TEXT
color: aqua;              /* text color */
background-color: black;  /* background color */

font-size: 20px;          /* size of text */
font-family: monospace;   /* style of text */
font-weight: bold;        /* thickness of text */

text-align: center;       /* left | center | right */
text-transform: uppercase; /* uppercase | lowercase */
text-decoration: none;    /* removes underline */

üß† Logic:
These affect how text looks, not layout.
=========================================================================

üì¶ BOX MODEL (MOST IMPORTANT CONCEPT)
Every element is a box:

| margin |
| border |
| padding |
| content |

üß± Padding (Inner Space)
padding: 20px;            /* space inside the element */
padding-top: 10px;
padding-right: 5px;
padding-bottom: 10px;
padding-left: 15px;

üß† Logic:
Padding increases space inside the box.

üëâ Reduce right padding only: padding-right: 5px;
==========================================================

üìê Margin (Outer Space)
margin: 20px;             /* space outside element */
margin: 100px auto;       /* center horizontally */

üß† Logic:
Margin controls distance from other elements.
=============================================================

üü® Border
border: 2px solid yellow;
border-radius: 20px;      /* rounded corners */
=============================================================

üìè WIDTH & HEIGHT
width: 600px;             /* fixed width */
max-width: 600px;         /* responsive limit */
height: 300px;

üß† Logic:
width ‚Üí strict
max-width ‚Üí flexible for mobile

‚úÖ BEST PRACTICE:
width: 90%;
max-width: 600px;
=============================================================

üß≤ DISPLAY (LAYOUT CONTROL)
display: block;           /* default for div */
display: inline;          /* no width/height */
display: inline-block;    /* inline + width */
display: none;            /* hides element */
==============================================================

üß≠ FLEXBOX (MOST USED IN REAL PROJECTS)
Parent
display: flex;            /* activates flexbox */
flex-direction: row;      /* row | column */
justify-content: center;  /* horizontal alignment */
align-items: center;      /* vertical alignment */
gap: 20px;                /* space between items */

üß† Logic:
justify-content ‚Üí main direction

align-items ‚Üí cross direction

Example (Logo + Text inline)
.heading {
  display: flex;          /* put items in one line */
  align-items: center;    /* vertically center */
  gap: 15px;              /* space between logo & text */
}

1Ô∏è‚É£ FLEXBOX GOLDEN RULE

üëâ Flexbox always works on TWO levels

Parent  ‚Üí controls layout
Children ‚Üí obey parent


So remember:

‚ùå Child cannot use flex without parent
‚úÖ Parent MUST have display: flex

2Ô∏è‚É£ TURN ON FLEXBOX (MANDATORY)
.container {
  display: flex;
}


Without this ‚Üí nothing works

3Ô∏è‚É£ FLEX DIRECTION (AXIS LOGIC)
flex-direction: row;    /* default ‚Üí left to right */
flex-direction: column; /* top to bottom */

Axis concept:

1. Row
Main axis ‚Üí horizontal
Cross axis ‚Üí vertical

2. Column
Main axis ‚Üí vertical
Cross axis ‚Üí horizontal

üß† THIS is why many people get confused.

4Ô∏è‚É£ JUSTIFY-CONTENT (MAIN AXIS)

Controls spacing on main axis

justify-content: flex-start;   /* start */
justify-content: center;       /* center */
justify-content: flex-end;     /* end */
justify-content: space-between;
justify-content: space-around;
justify-content: space-evenly;


üìå Example:

nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}

5Ô∏è‚É£ ALIGN-ITEMS (CROSS AXIS)

Controls alignment on cross axis

align-items: stretch;   /* default */
align-items: center;
align-items: flex-start;
align-items: flex-end;


üìå Center vertically:

.container {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

=======================================================

üñºÔ∏è IMAGE CONTROL
img {
  width: 70px;
  height: 70px;
  object-fit: contain;    /* no distortion */
}
=========================================================

üß† POSITIONING (ADVANCED)
position: relative;       /* base reference */
position: absolute;       /* move freely */
top: 10px;
right: 20px;

üß† Logic: absolute moves inside nearest relative
=========================================================

üé¨ TRANSITION & ANIMATION
transition: all 0.3s ease;

.card:hover {
  transform: scale(1.05); /* zoom effect */
}
üß† Logic: Smooth animation when state changes.
============================================================

üßæ LISTS
ul {
  list-style: none;       /* remove bullets */
}
===========================================================

üß© YOUR CARD EXAMPLE (FULL LOGIC)
.card {
  border: 5px solid yellow;   /* card outline */
  padding: 20px;             /* inner spacing */
  padding-right: 10px;       /* reduce right padding */
  margin: 100px auto;        /* center card */
  border-radius: 20px;       /* smooth corners */
  width: 90%;                /* responsive */
  max-width: 600px;          /* limit size */
}
===========================================================

üîü Z-INDEX (LAYER CONTROL)
z-index: 10;

Higher value = on top
=============================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ ANIMATIONS (ADVANCED)
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; }
}

.card {
  animation: fadeIn 1s ease;
}
===============================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ RESPONSIVE DESIGN
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .card {
    width: 95%;
  }
}
=============================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ SHADOWS
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
============================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ OVERFLOW
overflow: hidden;
overflow-y: scroll;
=============================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ CURSOR & POINTER
cursor: pointer;
==============================================================

üéØ HOW TO PRACTICE (IMPORTANT)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Change one property at a time
2Ô∏è‚É£ Observe what changed visually
3Ô∏è‚É£ Ask: ‚ÄúDid it affect size, position, or look?‚Äù
